"1021","SIGNATURE   NANCY WISER"
"1022","TITLE       TREASURER"
"1023","</TEXT>"
"1024","</DOCUMENT>"
"1025","<DOCUMENT>"
"1026","<TYPE>EX-99.77B ACCT LTTR"
"1027","<SEQUENCE>2"
"1028","<FILENAME>auditletter.txt"
"1029","<DESCRIPTION>AUDIT LETTER"
"1030","<TEXT>"
"1031","Report of Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm"
"1032","To the Board of Trustees and Shareholders of"
"1033","Wells Fargo Funds Trust:"
"1034","In planning and performing our audits of the financial"
"1035","statements of the Wells Fargo Intrinsic Small Cap Value"
"1036","Fund, Wells Fargo Small Cap Core Fund, Wells Fargo"
"1037","Small Cap Opportunities Fund, Wells Fargo Small Cap"
"1038","Value Fund, Wells Fargo Special Small Cap Value Fund,"
"1039","Wells Fargo Traditional Small Cap Growth Fund, Wells"
"1040","Fargo Precious Metals Fund, Wells Fargo Specialized"
"1041","Technology Fund and Wells Fargo Utility and"
"1042","Telecommunications Fund (the Funds), nine of the"
"1043","funds comprising the Wells Fargo Funds Trust, as of"
"1044","and for the year ended March 31, 2018, in accordance"
"1045","with the standards of the Public Company Accounting"
"1046","Oversight Board (United States), we considered the"
"1047","Funds internal control over financial reporting,"
"1048","including controls over safeguarding securities, as a"
"1049","basis for designing our auditing procedures for the"
"1050","purpose of expressing our opinion on the financial"
"1051","statements and to comply with the requirements of"
"1052","Form N-SAR, but not for the purpose of expressing an"
"1053","opinion on the effectiveness of the Funds internal"
"1054","control over financial reporting. Accordingly, we"
"1055","express no such opinion."
"1056","Management of the Funds is responsible for"
"1057","establishing and maintaining effective internal"
"1058","control over financial reporting. In fulfilling this"
"1059","responsibility, estimates and judgments by management"
"1060","are required to assess the expected benefits and"
"1061","related costs of controls. A funds internal control"
"1062","over financial reporting is a process designed to"
"1063","provide reasonable assurance regarding the"
"1064","reliability of financial reporting and the"
"1065","preparation of financial statements for external"
"1066","purposes in accordance with generally accepted"
"1067","accounting principles. A funds internal control over"
"1068","financial reporting includes those policies and"
"1069","procedures that (1) pertain to the maintenance of"
"1070","records that, in reasonable detail, accurately and"
"1071","fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of"
"1072","the assets of the fund; (2) provide reasonable"
"1073","assurance that transactions are recorded as necessary"
"1074","to permit preparation of financial statements in"
"1075","accordance with generally accepted accounting"
"1076","principles, and that receipts and expenditures of the"
"1077","fund are being made only in accordance with"
"1078","authorizations of management and trustees of the"
"1079","fund; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding"
"1080","prevention or timely detection of unauthorized"
"1081","acquisition, use, or disposition of the funds"
"1082","assets that could have a material effect on the"
"1083","financial statements."
"1084","Because of its inherent limitations, internal control"
"1085","over financial reporting may not prevent or detect"
"1086","misstatements. Also, projections of any evaluation of"
"1087","effectiveness to future periods are subject to the"
"1088","risk that controls may become inadequate because of"
"1089","changes in conditions, or that the degree of"
"1090","compliance with the policies or procedures may"
"1091","deteriorate."
"1092","A deficiency in internal control over financial"
"1093","reporting exists when the design or operation of a"
"1094","control does not allow management or employees, in"
"1095","the normal course of performing their assigned"
"1096","functions, to prevent or detect misstatements on a"
"1097","timely basis. A material weakness is a deficiency,"
"1098","or a combination of deficiencies, in internal"
"1099","control over financial reporting, such that there"
"1100","is a reasonable possibility that a material"
"1101","misstatement of the Funds annual or interim"
"1102","financial statements will not be prevented or"
"1103","detected on a timely basis."
"1104","Our consideration of the Funds internal control"
"1105","over financial reporting was for the limited"
"1106","purpose described in the first paragraph and would"
"1107","not necessarily disclose all deficiencies in"
"1108","internal control that might be material weaknesses"
"1109","under standards established by the Public Company"
"1110","Accounting Oversight Board (United States)."
"1111","However, we noted no deficiencies in the Funds"
"1112","internal control over financial reporting and its"
"1113","operation, including controls for over"
"1114","safeguarding securities that we consider to be a"
"1115","material weakness as defined above as of"
"1116","March 31, 2018."
"1117","This report is intended solely for the"
"1118","information and use of management and the Board"
"1119","of Trustees of Wells Fargo Funds Trust and the"
"1120","Securities and Exchange Commission and is not"
"1121","intended to be and should not be used by anyone"
"1122","other than these specified parties."
"1123","				KPMG LLP"
"1124","Boston, Massachusetts"
"1125","May 23, 2018"
"1126","</TEXT>"
"1127","</DOCUMENT>"
