"1688","Section 19. Questions of Interpretation. Any question of"
"1689","interpretation of any term or provision of this Agreement having a"
"1690","counterpart in or otherwise derived from a term or provision of the"
"1691","1940 Act shall be resolved by reference to such terms or provision"
"1692","of the 1940 Act and to interpretations thereof, if any, by the United"
"1693","States Courts or in the absence of any controlling decision of any"
"1694","such court, by rules, regulations or orders of the Commission,"
"1695","interpretations of the Commission or its staff, or Commission staff"
"1696","no-action letters, issued pursuant to the 1940 Act. In addition,"
"1697","where the effect of a requirement of the 1940 Act reflected in any"
"1698","provision of this Agreement is revised by rule, regulation or order"
"1699","of the Commission, such provision shall be deemed to incorporate"
"1700","the effect of such rule, regulation or order. The duties and"
"1701","obligations of the parties under this Agreement shall be governed"
"1702","by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of"
"1703","Delaware to the extent that state law is not preempted by the"
"1704","provisions of any law of the United States heretofore or hereafter"
"1705","enacted."
"1706","Section 20. Amendment of this Agreement. This"
"1707","Agreement supersedes the Amended and Restated Investment"
"1708","Advisory Agreement between the parties hereto dated August 6,"
"1709","2003, and amended as of October 1, 2005 and March 27, 2009, and"
"1710","combines the Fund-level administrative duties and fees of the"
"1711","Amended and Restated Administration Agreement between the"
"1712","parties hereto dated March 1, 2013 and amended as of March 25,"
"1713","2011. No provision of this Agreement may be changed, waived,"
"1714","discharged or terminated orally, but only by an instrument in"
"1715","writing signed by the party against which enforcement of the"
"1716","change, waiver, discharge or termination is sought. If shareholder"
"1717","approval of an amendment is required under the 1940 Act, no such"
"1718","amendment shall become effective until approved by a vote of the"
"1719","majority of the outstanding shares of the affected Funds."
"1720","Otherwise, a written amendment of this Agreement is effective"
"1721","upon the approval of the Board and the Manager."
"1722","Section 21. Wells Fargo Name. The Manager and the"
"1723","Trust each agree that the name Wells Fargo, which comprises a"
"1724","component of the Trust's name, is a property right of the parent of"
"1725","the Manager. The Trust agrees and consents that: (i) it will use the"
"1726","words Wells Fargo as a component of its corporate name, the"
"1727","name of any series or class, or all of the above, and for no other"
"1728","purpose; (ii) it will not grant to any third party the right to use the"
"1729","name Wells Fargo for any purpose; (iii) the Manager or any"
"1730","corporate affiliate of the Manager may use or grant to others the"
"1731","right to use the words Wells Fargo, or any combination or"
"1732","abbreviation thereof, as all or a portion of a corporate or business"
"1733","name or for any commercial purpose, other than a grant of such"
"1734","right to another registered investment company not advised by the"
"1735","Manager or one of its affiliates; and (iv) in the event that the"
"1736","Manager or an affiliate thereof is no longer acting as investment"
"1737","adviser to any Fund, the Trust shall, upon request by the Manager,"
"1738","promptly take such action as may be necessary to change its"
"1739","corporate name to one not containing the words Wells Fargo and"
"1740","following such change, shall not use the words Wells Fargo, or"
"1741","any combination thereof, as a part of its corporate name or for any"
"1742","other commercial purpose, and shall use its best efforts to cause its"
"1743","trustees, officers and shareholders to take any and all actions that"
"1744","the Manager may request to effect the foregoing and to reconvey to"
"1745","the Manager any and all rights to such words."
"1746","Section 22. Risk Acknowledgement. The Manager does"
"1747","not guarantee the future performance of the Funds or any specific"
"1748","level of performance, the success of any investment decision or"
"1749","strategy that the Manager may use, or the success of the Manager's"
"1750","overall management of the Funds. The Trust understands that"
"1751","investment decisions made for the Funds by the Manager are"
"1752","subject to various market, currency, economic and business risks,"
"1753","and that those investment decisions will not always be profitable."
"1754","The Manager will manage only the securities, cash and other"
"1755","investments for which management responsibility is delegated to it"
"1756","and which are held in the Funds' account(s) and, in making"
"1757","investment decisions for the Funds, the Manager will not consider"
"1758","any other securities, cash or other investments owned by the Trust."
