"2493","INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT AGREEMENT"
"2494","This INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT AGREEMENT (this Agreement)"
"2495","is made as of this 18th day of November, 2015,"
"2496","between Wells Fargo Funds Trust (the Trust), a statutory trust"
"2497","organized under the laws of the State of Delaware with its"
"2498","principal place of business at 525 Market Street, 12th Floor, San"
"2499","Francisco, California, 94105 and Wells Fargo Funds Management,"
"2500","LLC (the Manager), a limited liability company organized under"
"2501","the laws of the State of Delaware with its principal place of"
"2502","business at 525 Market Street, 12th Floor, San Francisco,"
"2503","California, 94105."
"2504","WHEREAS, the Trust is registered under the Investment"
"2505","Company Act of 1940, as amended (the 1940 Act) as an openend"
"2506","management investment company and is authorized to issue"
"2507","interests (as defined in the Trust's Declaration of Trust, as"
"2508","amended and supplemented from time to time), in separate series;"
"2509","WHEREAS, the Trust desires that the Manager provide"
"2510","investment management services consisting of advisory services"
"2511","and Fund-level (as opposed to class-level) administrative services"
"2512","to each series of the Trust listed on Schedule A hereto as such"
"2513","Schedule may be amended or supplemented from time to time by"
"2514","mutual agreement (each a Fund and collectively the Funds),"
"2515","and the Manager is willing to provide those services on the terms"
"2516","and conditions set forth in this Agreement; and"
"2517","WHEREAS, the Trust has entered into a separate Class-Level"
"2518","Administration Agreement with the Manager for the"
"2519","provision of class-level administrative services (Class-Level
Duties)."
"2520","NOW THEREFORE, the Trust and the Manager agree as follows:"
"2521","Section 1. Appointment of the Manager. The Trust is"
"2522","engaged in the business of investing and reinvesting its assets in"
"2523","securities of the type and in accordance with the limitations"
"2524","specified in its Declaration of Trust, as amended and supplemented"
"2525","from time to time, By-Laws (if any) and Registration Statement"
"2526","filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission (the"
"2527","Commission) under the 1940 Act and the Securities Act of 1933"
"2528","(the Securities Act), including any representations made in the"
"2529","prospectus and statement of additional information relating to the"
"2530","Funds contained therein and as may be amended or supplemented"
"2531","from time to time, all in such manner and to such extent as may"
"2532","from time to time be authorized by the Trust's Board of Trustees"
"2533","(the Board). The Board is authorized to issue any unissued"
"2534","shares in any number of additional classes or series."
"2535","The investment authority granted to the Manager shall"
"2536","include the authority to exercise whatever powers the Trust may"
"2537","possess with respect to any of its assets held by the Funds,"
"2538","including, but not limited to, the power to exercise rights, options,"
"2539","warrants, conversion privileges, redemption privileges, and to"
"2540","tender securities pursuant to a tender offer, and participate in class"
"2541","actions and other legal proceedings on behalf of the Funds."
"2542","The Trust hereby appoints the Manager, subject to the"
"2543","direction and control of the Board, to manage the investment and"
"2544","reinvestment of the assets in the Funds and, without limiting the"
"2545","generality of the foregoing, to provide the other services specified"
"2546","in Section 2 hereof."
"2547","The Trust hereby appoints the Manager to provide the"
"2548","Fund-level duties and services as set forth in Section 2(b) hereof,"
"2549","for the compensation and on the terms herein provided, and the"
"2550","Manager hereby accepts such appointment."
"2551","Section 2. Duties of the Manager."
"2552","(a) Advisory Services."
"2553","(i) The Manager shall make decisions with respect to"
"2554","all purchases and sales of securities and other investment assets for"
"2555","the Funds. Among other things, the Manager shall make all"
"2556","decisions with respect to the allocation of the Funds' investments"
"2557","in various securities or other assets, in investment styles and, if"
"2558","applicable, in other investment companies or pooled vehicles in"
"2559","which a Fund may invest. To carry out such decisions, the"
"2560","Manager is hereby authorized, as agent and attorney-in-fact for the"
"2561","Trust, for the account of, at the risk of and in the name of the Trust,"
"2562","to place orders and issue instructions with respect to those"
"2563","transactions of the Funds. In all purchases, sales and other"
"2564","transactions in securities for the Funds, the Manager is authorized"
"2565","to exercise full discretion and act for the Trust in the same manner"
"2566","and with the same force and effect as the Trust might or could do"
"2567","with respect to such purchases, sales or other transactions, as well"
"2568","as with respect to all other things necessary or incidental to the"
"2569","furtherance or conduct of such purchases, sales or other"
"2570","transactions."
"2571","(ii) The Manager will report to the Board at each"
"2572","regular meeting thereof regarding the investment performance of"
"2573","the Funds since the prior report, and will also keep the Board"
"2574","informed of important developments affecting the Trust, each Fund"
"2575","and the Manager, and on its own initiative will furnish the Board"
"2576","from time to time with such information as the Manager may"
"2577","believe appropriate, whether concerning the individual companies"
"2578","whose securities are held by a Fund, the industries in which they"
"2579","engage, or the economic, social or political conditions prevailing in"
"2580","each country in which a Fund maintains investments. The"
"2581","Manager will also furnish the Board with such statistical and"
"2582","analytical information with respect to securities in the Funds as the"
"2583","Manager may believe appropriate or as the Board reasonably may"
"2584","request."
"2585","The Manager shall promptly notify the Trust of (A) any"
"2586","changes regarding the Manager that would impact disclosure in the"
"2587","Trust's Registration Statement, or (B) any violation of any"
"2588","requirement, provision, policy or restriction that the Manager is"
"2589","required to comply with under Section 6 of this Agreement. The"
"2590","Manager shall immediately notify the Trust of any legal process"
"2591","served upon it in connection with its activities hereunder, including"
"2592","any legal process served upon it on behalf of the Funds or the"
"2593","Trust."
"2594","(iii) The Manager may from time to time employ or subcontract"
"2595","the services to certain persons as the Manager believes to"
"2596","be appropriate or necessary to assist in the execution of the"
"2597","Manager's duties hereunder; provided, however, that the"
"2598","employment or sub-contracting with any such person shall not"
"2599","relieve the Manager of its responsibilities or liabilities hereunder"
"2600","and provided further that the Manager shall not have the authority"
"2601","to sub-contract advisory responsibilities without the consent of the"
"2602","Trust. The cost of performance of such duties will be borne and"
"2603","paid by the Manager. No obligation may be imposed on the Trust"
"2604","in any such respect."
"2605","The Manager shall supervise and monitor the activities of its"
"2606","representatives, personnel, sub-contractors, and agents in connection"
"2607","with the execution of its duties and obligations hereunder. The"
"2608","appropriate personnel of the Manager will be made available to"
"2609","consult with the Board at reasonable times and upon reasonable"
"2610","notice concerning the business of the Trust."
"2611","(iv) The Manager shall maintain records relating to"
"2612","portfolio transactions and the placing and allocation of brokerage"
"2613","orders as are required to be maintained by the Trust under the 1940"
"2614","Act. The Manager shall prepare and maintain, or cause to be"
"2615","prepared and maintained, in such form, for such periods and in"
"2616","such locations as may be required by applicable law, all documents"
"2617","and records relating to the services provided by the Manager"
"2618","pursuant to this Agreement required to be prepared and maintained"
"2619","by the Trust pursuant to the rules and regulations of any national,"
"2620","state, or local government entity with jurisdiction over the Trust,"
"2621","including the Commission and the Internal Revenue Service. The"
"2622","books and records pertaining to the Trust which are in possession"
"2623","of the Manager shall be the property of the Trust. The Trust, or the"
"2624","Trust's authorized representatives, shall have access to such books"
"2625","and records at all times during the Manager's normal business"
"2626","hours. Upon the reasonable request of the Trust, copies of any"
"2627","such books and records shall be provided promptly by the Manager"
"2628","to the Trust or the Trust's authorized representatives."
"2629","(v) With respect to a Fund, the Manager shall have no"
"2630","duties or obligations pursuant to this Agreement other than as"
"2631","specified in Section 2(b) hereof, during any period during which"
"2632","the Fund invests all (or substantially all) of its investment assets in"
"2633","a registered, open-end management investment company, or"
"2634","separate series thereof, in accordance with Section 12(d)(1)(E)"
"2635","under the 1940 Act."
"2636","(b) Fund-Level Administrative Services. The Manager shall, at"
"2637","its expense, provide the following Fund-level administrative"
"2638","services in connection with the operations of the Trust and the"
"2639","Funds, to the extent such services are not provided to a Class of a"
"2640","Fund and covered under the Funds' Class-Level Administration"
"2641","Agreement:"
"2642","i) coordinate, supervise and make all payments to the"
"2643","Funds' transfer agent and various sub-transfer"
"2644","agents and omnibus account servicers and recordkeepers;"
"2645","ii) receive and tabulate shareholder votes;"
"2646","iii) furnish statistical and research data;"
"2647","iv) coordinate (or assist in) the preparation and filing"
"2648","with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission"
"2649","(SEC) of registration statements, notices,"
"2650","shareholder reports, and other material required to"
"2651","be filed under applicable laws;"
"2652","v) prepare and file with the states registration"
"2653","statements, notices, reports, and other material"
"2654","required to be filed under applicable laws;"
"2655","vi) prepare and file Form 24F-2s and N-SARs;"
"2656","vii) review bills submitted to the Funds and, upon"
"2657","determining that a bill is appropriate, allocate"
"2658","amounts to the appropriate Funds and instruct the"
"2659","Funds' custodian to pay such bills;"
"2660","viii) coordinate (or assist in) the preparation of reports"
"2661","and other information materials regarding the"
"2662","Funds, including prospectuses, proxies and other"
"2663","shareholder communications;"
"2664","ix) prepare expense table and performance information"
"2665","for annual updates;"
"2666","x) provide legal and regulatory advice to the Funds in"
"2667","connection with its other administrative functions,"
"2668","including assignment of matters to outside legal"
"2669","counsel on behalf of the Trust and supervision of"
"2670","the work of such counsel;"
"2671","xi) provide office facilities and clerical support for the"
"2672","Funds;"
"2673","xii) develop and implement procedures for monitoring"
"2674","compliance with regulatory requirements and"
"2675","compliance with the Funds' investment objectives,"
"2676","policies and restrictions;"
"2677","xiii) serve as liaison between the Funds and their"
"2678","independent auditors;"
"2679","xiv) prepare and file tax returns;"
"2680","xv) review payments of Fund expenses;"
"2681","xvi) prepare expense budgeting and accruals;"
"2682","xvii) provide communication, coordination, and"
"2683","supervision services with regard to the Funds'"
"2684","transfer agent, custodian, fund accountant, any coadministrators,"
"2685","and other service organizations that"
"2686","render recordkeeping or shareholder communication"
"2687","services;"
"2688","xviii) provide information to the Funds' distributor"
"2689","concerning fund performance and administration;"
"2690","xix) provide reports to the Funds' board of directors"
"2691","regarding its activities;"
"2692","xx) assist in the preparation and assembly of meeting"
"2693","materials, including comparable fee information, as"
"2694","required, for the Funds' board of directors; and"
"2695","xxi) provide any other administrative services"
"2696","reasonably necessary for the operation of the Funds"
"2697","other than those services that are to be provided by"
"2698","the Trust's transfer and dividend disbursing agent,"
"2699","custodian, and fund accountant, provided that"
"2700","nothing in this Agreement shall be deemed to"
"2701","require Funds Management to provide any services"
"2702","that may not be provided by it under applicable"
"2703","banking laws and regulations."
"2704","In performing all Fund-level administrative services under"
"2705","this Section 2(b), the Manager shall: (a) act in conformity with the"
"2706","Trust's Declaration of Trust (and By-Laws, if any), the 1940 Act,"
"2707","and any other applicable laws as may be amended from time to"
"2708","time, and all relevant rules thereunder, and with the Trust's"
"2709","registration statement under the Securities Act of 1933 and the"
"2710","1940 Act, as may be amended from time to time; (b) consult and"
"2711","coordinate with legal counsel to the Trust as necessary and"
"2712","appropriate; and (c) advise and report to the Trust and its legal"
"2713","counsel, as necessary and appropriate, with respect to any"
"2714","compliance or other matters that come to its attention."
"2715","In connection with its duties under this Section 2(b), the"
"2716","Manager may, at its own expense, enter into sub-administration"
"2717","agreements with other service providers, provided that each such"
"2718","service provider agrees with Manager to comply with this"
"2719","Agreement and all relevant provisions of the 1940 Act and any"
"2720","other applicable laws as may be amended from time to time, and"
"2721","all relevant rules thereunder. Manager will provide the Trust with"
"2722","a copy of each sub-administration agreement it executes relating to"
"2723","the Trust. Manager will be liable for acts or omissions of any such"
"2724","sub-administrators under the standards of care described herein"
"2725","under Section 11."
