"2780","any rules and regulations adopted thereunder."
"2781","Section 7. Proxies. The Manager shall have responsibility"
"2782","to vote proxies solicited with respect to issuers of securities in"
"2783","which assets of the Funds are invested in accordance with the"
"2784","Trust's policies on proxy voting."
"2785","Section 8. Broker-Dealer Relationships. In connection"
"2786","with the purchase and sale of securities for the Funds, the Manager"
"2787","is responsible for broker-dealer selection and negotiation of"
"2788","brokerage commission rates. The Manager's primary"
"2789","consideration in effecting a security transaction will be to obtain"
"2790","the best price and execution. In selecting a broker-dealer to"
"2791","execute each particular transaction for a Fund, the Manager will"
"2792","consider among other things: the best net price available, the"
"2793","reliability, integrity and financial condition of the broker-dealer;"
"2794","the size of and difficulty in executing the order; and the value of"
"2795","the expected contribution of the broker-dealer to the Fund on a"
"2796","continuing basis. Accordingly, the price to the Fund in any"
"2797","transaction may be less favorable than that available from another"
"2798","broker-dealer if the difference is reasonably justified by other"
"2799","aspects of the portfolio execution services offered. Subject to such"
"2800","policies as the Board may from time to time determine, the"
"2801","Manager shall not be deemed to have acted unlawfully or to have"
"2802","breached any duty created by this Agreement or otherwise solely"
"2803","by reason of having caused a Fund to pay a broker or dealer that"
"2804","provides brokerage and research services to the Manager an"
"2805","amount of commission for effecting a portfolio investment"
"2806","transaction in excess of the amount of commission another broker"
"2807","or dealer would have charged for effecting that transaction, if the"
"2808","Manager determines in good faith that such amount of commission"
"2809","was reasonable in relation to the value of the brokerage and"
"2810","research services provided by such broker or dealer, viewed in"
"2811","terms of either that particular transaction or the overall"
"2812","responsibilities of the Manager with respect to the Fund and to"
"2813","other clients of the Manager. The Manager is further authorized to"
"2814","allocate the orders placed by it on behalf of the Funds to brokers"
"2815","and dealers who also provide brokerage and research services"
"2816","within the meaning of Section 28(e) of the Securities Exchange"
"2817","Act of 1934 and in compliance therewith. Such allocation shall be"
"2818","in such amounts and proportions as the Manager shall determine"
"2819","and the Manager will report on said allocations regularly to the"
"2820","Board, indicating the brokers to whom such allocations have been"
"2821","made and the basis therefore."
"2822","Section 9. Expenses. All of the ordinary business"
"2823","expenses incurred in the operations of the Funds and the offering"
"2824","of their shares shall be borne by the Funds unless specifically"
"2825","provided otherwise in this Agreement. The expenses borne by the"
"2826","Trust include, but are not limited to, brokerage commissions, taxes,"
"2827","legal, auditing or governmental fees, the cost of preparing share"
"2828","certificates, custodian, transfer agent and shareholder service agent"
"2829","costs, expense of issue, sale, redemption and repurchase of shares,"
"2830","expenses of registering and qualifying shares for sale, expenses"
"2831","relating to trustees and shareholder meetings, the cost of preparing"
"2832","and distributing reports and notices to shareholders, the fees and"
"2833","other expenses incurred by the Funds in connection with"
"2834","membership in investment company organizations and the cost of"
"2835","printing copies of prospectuses and statements of additional"
"2836","information distributed to the Funds' shareholders. In addition to"
"2837","the fees described in Section 10 of this Agreement, the Trust (or its"
"2838","other service providers, as may be provided pursuant to their"
"2839","respective agreements and contracts with the Trust) shall pay all of"
"2840","its Fund-level expenses which are not expressly assumed by the"
"2841","Manager pursuant to Section 2(b) or otherwise hereunder. The"
"2842","Fund-level expenses of legal counsel and accounting experts"
"2843","retained by the Manager, after consulting with the Trust's legal"
"2844","counsel and independent auditors, as may be reasonably necessary"
"2845","or appropriate for the performance by the Manager of its duties"
"2846","under this Agreement, shall be deemed to be Fund-level expenses"
"2847","of, and shall be paid for by, the Trust."
"2848","The Manager shall pay its own expenses in connection with"
"2849","the services to be provided by it pursuant to this Agreement and"
"2850","shall, at its own expense, provide its own office space, facilities"
"2851","and equipment. In addition, the Manager shall be responsible for"
"2852","reasonable out-of-pocket costs and expenses incurred by the Trust:"
"2853","(a) to amend the Trust's registration statement or supplement the"
"2854","Fund's prospectus, and circulate the same, to reflect a change in"
"2855","the personnel of the Manager responsible for making investment"
"2856","decisions in relation to a Fund; (b) to obtain approval required by"
"2857","the 1940 Act of a new sub-advisory agreement as a result of a"
"2858","change in control (as such term in defined in Section 2(a)(9) of"
"2859","the 1940 Act) of the Manager, or to otherwise comply with the"
"2860","1940 Act, the Securities Act, or any other applicable statute, law,"
"2861","rule or regulation, as a result of such change; or (c) to meet other"
"2862","legal or regulatory obligations caused by actions of the Manager."
"2863","Section 10. Compensation."
"2864","(a) As compensation for the investment management services"
"2865","provided under this Agreement, the Trust shall pay the"
"2866","Manager fees, payable monthly, at the annual rates"
"2867","indicated on Schedule A hereto, as such Schedule may be"
"2868","amended or supplemented from time to time. The fees"
"2869","payable pursuant to this Paragraph shall be calculated based"
"2870","on the average daily value (as determined on each business"
"2871","day at the time set forth in the Prospectus for determining"
"2872","net asset value per share) of each Fund's net assets, as"
"2873","appropriate, during the preceding month. If the fee payable"
"2874","to the Manager pursuant to this Paragraph begins to accrue"
"2875","before the end of any month or if this Agreement"
"2876","terminates before the end of any month, the fee for the"
"2877","period from the effective date to the end of that month or"
"2878","from the beginning of that month to the termination date,"
"2879","respectively, shall be prorated according to the proportion"
"2880","that the period bears to the full month in which the"
"2881","effectiveness or termination occurs. For purposes of"
"2882","calculating each such monthly fee, the value of each Fund's"
"2883","net assets shall be computed in the manner specified in that"
"2884","Fund's registration statement as then on file with the SEC"
"2885","for the computation of the value of the Fund's net assets in"
"2886","connection with the determination of the net asset value of"
"2887","Fund shares. For purposes of this Agreement, a business
day for a Fund is any day that the Fund is open for"
"2888","trading;"
"2889","(b) No fee, other than the management fee payable monthly, at"
"2890","the annual rates indicated on Schedule A hereto, as such"
"2891","Schedule may be amended or supplemented from time to"
"2892","time, payable for the Fund-level administrative services set"
"2893","forth in Section 2(b) of this Agreement, shall be payable"
"2894","hereunder with respect to a Fund during any period in"
"2895","which the Fund invests all (or substantially all) of its"
"2896","investment assets in a single registered, open-end"
"2897","management investment company, or a single separate"
"2898","series thereof, in accordance with Section 12(d)(1)(E)"
"2899","under the 1940 Act (a Master-Feeder Fund structure);"
"2900","(c) The Manager shall receive a fee as specified below for"
"2901","investment management services consisting of both Fundlevel"
"2902","administrative services and asset allocation services if"
"2903","a Fund in a Master-Feeder Fund structure coverts to a Fund"
"2904","that invests some or all of its investment assets in two or"
"2905","more registered, open-end management investment"
"2906","companies, or separate series thereof, in each case, in"
"2907","accordance with Section 12(d)(1)(G) under the Act, the"
"2908","rules thereunder or an exemptive order issued by the"
"2909","Commission exempting the Fund from the provisions of"
"2910","Section 12(d)(1)(A) under the Act (a Fund of Funds
structure)."
