"2916","Section 11. Standard of Care. The Trust will expect of"
"2917","the Manager, and the Manager will give the Trust the benefit of,"
"2918","the Manager's best judgment and efforts in rendering its services to"
"2919","the Trust, and the Manager shall not be liable hereunder for any"
"2920","mistake in judgment. In the absence of willful misfeasance, bad"
"2921","faith, negligence or reckless disregard of obligations or duties"
"2922","hereunder on the part of the Manager or any of its officers,"
"2923","directors, employees or agents, the Manager shall not be subject to"
"2924","liability to the Trust or to any other person for any act or omission"
"2925","in the course of, or connected with, rendering services hereunder or"
"2926","for any losses that may be sustained in the purchase, holding or"
"2927","sale of any security."
"2928","Section 12. Non-Exclusivity. The services of the"
"2929","Manager to the Funds are not to be deemed to be exclusive, and the"
"2930","Manager shall be free to render investment management or other"
"2931","services to others (including other investment companies) and to"
"2932","engage in other activities. It is understood and agreed that officers"
"2933","or directors of the Manager may serve as officers and directors of"
"2934","the Trust, and that officers or directors of the Trust may serve as"
"2935","officers or directors of the Manager, to the extent that such services"
"2936","may be permitted by law, and that the officers and directors of the"
"2937","Manager are not prohibited from engaging in any other business"
"2938","activity or from rendering services to any other person, or from"
"2939","serving as partners, officers, directors or trustees of any other firm"
"2940","or trust, including other investment advisory companies."
"2941","Section 13. Records. The Manager shall, with respect to"
"2942","orders the Manager places for the purchase and sale of portfolio"
"2943","securities of the Funds, maintain or arrange for the maintenance of"
"2944","the documents and records required pursuant to Rule 31a-1 under"
"2945","the 1940 Act as well as such records as the Funds' administrator"
"2946","reasonably requests to be maintained, including, but not limited to,"
"2947","trade tickets and confirmations for portfolio trades. All such"
"2948","records shall be maintained in a form acceptable to the Trust and in"
"2949","compliance with the provisions of Rule 31a-1 or any successor"
"2950","rule. All such records will be the property of the Trust and will be"
"2951","made available for inspection and use by the Trust and its"
"2952","authorized representatives."
"2953","Section 14. Term and Approval. This Agreement shall"
"2954","become effective with respect to a Fund after approval in"
"2955","accordance with the requirements of the 1940 Act, and executed by"
"2956","the Manager and the Trust, and shall thereafter continue from year"
"2957","to year, provided that the continuation of the Agreement is"
"2958","specifically approved in accordance with the requirements of the"
"2959","1940 Act, which currently requires that the continuation be"
"2960","approved at least annually:"
"2961","(a) by the Board, or by the vote of a majority of the
outstanding voting securities of the Fund (as defined in"
"2962","Section 2(a)(42) of the 1940 Act), and"
"2963","(b) by the affirmative vote of a majority of the Trust's Trustees"
"2964","who are not parties to this Agreement or interested
persons (as defined in the 1940 Act) of a party to this"
"2965","Agreement (other than as Trustees of the Trust), by votes"
"2966","cast in person at a meeting specifically called for such"
"2967","purpose."
"2968","Section 15. Termination. As required under the 1940"
"2969","Act, this Agreement may be terminated with respect to a Fund at"
"2970","any time, without the payment of any penalty, by vote of the Board"
"2971","or by vote of a majority of a Fund's outstanding voting securities,"
"2972","or by the Manager, on sixty (60) days' written notice to the other"
"2973","party. The notice provided for herein may be waived by the party"
"2974","entitled to receipt thereof. This Agreement shall automatically"
"2975","terminate in the event of its assignment, the term assignment for"
"2976","purposes of this paragraph having the meaning defined in Section"
"2977","2(a)(4) of the 1940 Act, as it may be interpreted by the"
"2978","Commission or its staff in interpretive releases, or by the"
"2979","Commission staff in no-action letters issued under the 1940 Act."
"2980","This Agreement may also be terminated immediately by the"
"2981","Trust or the Manager in the event that either party (i) breaches a"
"2982","material term of this Agreement; or (ii) commits a material"
"2983","violation of any governing law or regulation; or (iii) engages in"
"2984","conduct that would have a material adverse effect upon the"
"2985","reputation or business prospects of such other party."
